[BLOCKER] `docs/design/2026-04-27-synthetic-playtest-implementation-plan.md` lines 43-59 and T1 step 14 are not executable in this repo environment. The plan uses Bash-only review commands (`/tmp/task-diff.patch`, `mkdir -p`, `$(date ...)`, shell `PROMPT=...`, background `&`) even though the stated environment is Windows/PowerShell, and step 4/5 are still “Wait via background poller” / “Synthesize REVIEW.md” placeholders. Because multi-CLI review is mandatory, the engineer cannot actually run the review loop as written.

[BLOCKER] The plan still fails the writing-plans/TDD concreteness bar in multiple places. T2 step 3 ends with `// ...`, T2 step 4 is entirely `/* ... */` stubs for stop reasons and failure modes, and T3 steps 2-10 are headings or one-line descriptions with no concrete code, run-to-fail commands, run-to-pass commands, or commit text (see lines 539, 543-562, 787-825). That also means several spec-required cases are not planned in executable detail, including start-poisoned rejection, `sourceLabel` default/override, partial-submit-then-throw, and full-bundle production determinism.

[HIGH] T2 step 5 breaks the `snapshotInterval` contract. `snapshotInterval: snapshotInterval ?? 1000` converts an explicit `null` into `1000`, but both the current `SessionRecorderConfig` contract in `src/session-recorder.ts` and design §7 say `null` disables periodic snapshots. The harness needs to preserve `null` and add a test for that path.

[HIGH] The doc-with-the-code plan is incomplete for the public surface that ships in T2. The plan creates `docs/guides/synthetic-playtest.md` in T2 (lines 469/715), but defers `docs/README.md` indexing to T3 (line 819) and only mentions the README Feature Overview row in the final checklist (line 842). T1/T2 also only plan README badge bumps (lines 415 and 725) even though new top-level exports are landing. Per AGENTS.md, the canonical README/docs indexes need to update in the same commit as the new API/guide, not one task later.

[HIGH] The concrete T3 positive determinism test is wrong against current engine behavior. In lines 757-773 it emits `spawn` commands via `randomPolicy` but never registers a `spawn` handler. Current `World.processCommands()` turns a missing handler into a tick failure and poisons the world (`src/world.ts`, missing-handler path), so `expect(result.ok).toBe(true)` and `selfCheck().ok === true` cannot both hold. The setup needs a handler or a different command path.


